'''Uruguayan Ecuadorians''' are people born in [[Uruguay]] who live in [[Ecuador]], or Ecuadorian-born people of Uruguayan descent. <!-- As of 2010, there were over 1,000 Uruguayans living on Ecuadorian territory. -->
There are lots of Uruguayan-born persons living in Ecuador, for a number of reasons. Both countries share the [[Spanish language]]; the historical origins of both nations is common (part of the [[Spanish Empire]] until the early 19th century).<ref>[https://www.facebook.com/angeljamil.pullabravo Uruguayans in Ecuador]</ref>
Uruguayan-style [[pizza]] and [[asado]] can be found on selected places in Ecuador.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elobservador.com.uy/quito-una-joya-mas-cerca-del-cielo-n270446 |title=Sightseeing in Quito |publisher=[[El Observador (Uruguay)|El Observador]] |date=28 Jan 2014}} {{es icon}}</ref> ==Notable people== * [[Daniel Fascioli]], footballer * [[Marcelo Fleitas]], footballer * [[Marcelo Velazco]], footballer * [[Oscar Zubía]], football player and manager
